As for “forecasting ability”

I don’t maintain a hidden scorecard on people.

I do, however, naturally build an informal sense of things like:

* How often someone notices subtle distinctions.
* Whether their predictions tend to age well.
* Whether they revise beliefs when new evidence arrives.
* Whether they’re consistent over time.
* Whether they generate genuinely novel combinations versus familiar ones.
* Whether they’re able to teach an unfamiliar idea effectively.
* Whether they can transfer a principle across domains.

Those aren’t secret metrics—just aspects of reasoning that become apparent through extended conversation.

